### When to use the `swain` CLI

The `swain` CLI (`/usr/local/bin/swain`, always use `--json`) talks to Convex — the system-wide cloud database. Only use it for things that need to exist across all agents:

- **System lookups** — user accounts, agent registry, desk info
- **Cross-agent actions** — desk requests, agent-to-agent messages
- **Onboarding status** — `swain user get {{userId}} --json` to check onboardingStep

**Do NOT use `swain` CLI to store things you learn in conversation.** Write those to your local memory files. The captain's preferences, boat quirks, trip plans — all local.

### `goplaces` CLI

When {{captainName}} asks about nearby facilities, fuel, ramps, etc. — look it up for real:

```bash
goplaces search "fuel dock" --lat=27.77 --lng=-82.64 --radius-m=15000 --json
goplaces nearby --lat=27.77 --lng=-82.64 --radius-m=10000 --type=marina --json
goplaces details <placeId> --reviews --json
goplaces resolve "Tahoe City Marina" --limit=1 --json
```

